cvpiaData
  • Reference

Load SIT Model Inputs for Years 1980-1999

returns list of data values used by model

load_baseline_data(species)

Arguments

species

Call function with one of the following options to load species specific model inputs: 'fall', 'winter', 'spring', 'steelhead'

Value

list of model inputs

Details

The list returned contains the following data:

  • Miscellaneous model inputs

  • Proportion of flow diverted for each watershed

  • Total flow diverted for each watershed

  • Proportion of flow diverted in the North and South deltas

  • Total flow diverted in the North and South deltas

  • Monthly mean temperature during juvenile outmigration in each watershed

  • Monthly mean temperature during juvenile outmigration in the deltas

  • Total inflow in the deltas

  • Proportion of Sacramento River into Yolo Bypass

  • Proportion of Sacramento River into Sutter Bypass

  • Instream habitat areas for each watershed

  • Habitat areas for the deltas

  • Floodplain habitat areas for each watershed

  • Yearly record of bypasses overtopped in October of November

  • Accumulated degree days for adults before spawning

  • Proportion of flows at tributary junction from natal watershed in October

  • Upper Sacramento flow

  • Flow at Georgiana slough

  • Total and proportion number of days the cross channel gates are typically closed per month

  • Temperature effect on egg mortality

Examples

# place these two lines within the SIT Salmon Population Model function to load the data
all_inputs <- cvpiaData::load_baseline_data('fall')
list2env(all_inputs, envir = environment())
#> Error in list2env(all_inputs, envir = environment()): first argument must be a named list
